Hair

Makeup

This is the makeup used for all dances unless otherwise noted.

Click here for Makeup Document

Eyes
Eye Shadow:
  • Ulta Morphe 25A Copper Spice:
  • Eyelid: Suede- row 5 middle
  • Crease: Tan Lines - row 3 middle
  • -OR-
  • Ulta Morphe 9A Always Golden Palette
  • Eyelid: 'Connection'
  • Crease: 'Witness'
  • Use a dark shadow to line the lower lash line with an angled liner brush and black eyeliner on the top lash line.
Eye Liner:
Black liner on the top lash line in pencil, liquid or gel. Should be a thin/medium line. No Wings.
Lashes:
Ardell Brand in one of the following styles #105, #107 or #122 (no rhinestones or color on lashes). Please advise that lashes may need to be trimmed (on the outer edge) to best fit dancers eye shape. *(MINIS will NOT wear false lashes but must wear black mascara.)
Lash Glue:
Duo Adhesive (Recommended)
Recommended:
  • Makeup Brushes: Morphe Brushes at Ulta; good quality at an affordable price.
Blush
Color:
A rose shade that compliments your dancer's complexion
Lips
Brand:
MAC
Color:
Rebel
Optional:
MAC Nightingale Lip Pencil to match lipstick.)
Foundation:
  • choose a shade that matches skin tone, is long lasting and has a matte finish (not dewy, luminous or shiny).
Powder:
  • to set the foundation and to keep skin matte in a translucent or skin matching shade
Optional
  • Bronzer to enhance your dancer's skin tone.
Routines to Display:

Check to display in 'Routines' Tab
